lead_paragraph: Australia became the first Olympic champions in women's rugby sevens when they ran out convincing 24-17 winners over trans-Tasman neighbours New Zealand in the gold medal final at the Deodoro Stadium in Rio on Monday.

headline.print_headline: Australia Clinch Inaugural Women's Sevens Gold
